    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, wash your<strong> lettuce</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper and shred finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span></strong>into wedges</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> (not a fan of raw garlic? Just add a little!) with your<strong> mayo </strong>in a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water </strong>– this is your <strong>garlic mayo</strong></p>",
